Kim Jong Il's Feats for Reunification Praised 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 28 (KCNA) -- In the joint New Year editorial the Workers' Party of Korea expressed the steadfast will to achieve the national reunification in the present generation, true to President Kim Il Sung's last instructions for reunification, and on this basis made a patriotic proposal for glorifying the June 15 era of reunification by attaching importance to the nation, defending peace and achieving unity.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In response to this proposal, the government, political parties and organizations of the DPRK made public a joint statement calling on the Koreans to make this year a year of turning point in history whereby to usher in the new annals for national reunification.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The joint statement has served as a banner of powerfully encouraging all Koreans in the north and the south and overseas to the dynamic nationwide movement for glorifying the June 15 era of reunification, says Rodong Sinmun Friday in a signed article.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the joint statement attracted positive support and approval from all Koreans and the Koreans in the north and the south and overseas turned out as one in the drive to glorify the June 15 era of reunification from the outset of this year, the article goes on:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Not a few achievements have been made in the development of the inter-Korean relations this year.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Thanks to the DPRK's patriotic will for reunification and initiative measures, there took place such talks of various forms between the north and the south as the premier-level talks, defence minister-level talks, ministerial-level talks, general-level military talks and the Red Cross talks. The agreements reached at the talks helped reconnect the severed railways between the north and the south and activate the north-south economic cooperation projects.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is entirely thanks to the tested and distinguished leadership of Kim Jong Il that the Korean nation's movement for national reunification has advanced as required by the times and desired by Koreans.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Firmly resolved to advance the June 15 era of reunification on a new high stage, he provided the historic inter-Korean summit in October and the adoption of the October 4 Declaration for the Development of North-South Relations and Peace and Prosperity. The adoption of the Oct. 4 declaration was one more event to be specially recorded in the history of the nation as the north and the south ushered in an era of national prosperity, a new history of the movement for independent reunification under the uplifted banner of "By our nation itself."&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The June 15 era of reunification advancing under the uplifted banner of "By our nation itself" will surely greet the dawn of reunified Korea in the near future as Kim Jong Il, the sun of the nation and the lodestar of national reunification, is wisely leading the cause of reunification.

Japan Urged to Settle Its Past Crimes, to Begin with 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 28 (KCNA) -- If there be politicians who know about politics and are able to foresee a future in Japan, they had better have a proper view on history, correctly judge the issue of history and swim with the trend of the times. Rodong Sinmun today urges this in a signed article.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As commented by the fair world public, the primary task facing Japan today is to liquidate its inglorious past as early as possible.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Redressing the past wrongs is a legal and moral responsibility Japan assumed before the times and history.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 With nothing can Japan cover up the criminal aggression perpetrated by the Japanese imperialists against Korea in the past. It is under obligation to settle this most hideous crime without fail no matter how much water may flow under the bridge. The Japanese reactionaries have persistently refused to repent of and apologize for this crime and played sleight of hand to keep it buried into oblivion.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The ruling quarters and political parties in Japan keep mum about the issue of redeeming Japan's past crimes, while wasting time with the argument about the issue of adopting a new "law on special measures against terrorism."&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If there be any politicians capable of foreseeing a future in Japan, they should propose the issue of settling its past war crimes and turning over a new leaf and kick off a political debate on it.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan would be well advised to stop rummaging through the cesspool of militaristic politics giving off bad smell but be sensitive to the times, properly judge the world and make a fresh start.

Floral Basket and Congratulatory Letter to Kim Jong Il from Military Attaches Corps 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 28 (KCNA) -- Leader Kim Jong Il was presented with a floral basket and a congratulatory letter by the military attaches corps here on the occasion of the New Year, Juche 97 (2008).&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The floral basket and congratulatory letter were conveyed to an official concerned by Military Attache of the Vietnamese embassy Dau Xuan Long who is doyen of the corps on Friday.

Floral Basket to Kim Jong Il from Zhang Weihua's Family 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 28 (KCNA) -- Leader Kim Jong Il was presented with a floral basket by the family of Zhang Weihua, an anti-Japanese revolutionary martyr, on Friday on the occasion of the New Year, Juche 97 (2008).&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Written on the ribbon of the floral basket were letters reading "We wholeheartedly wish the great leader Comrade Kim Jong Il good health".

Doctorate of Linguistics Conferred upon Dean of Faculty of Yanbian University of China 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 28 (KCNA) -- A doctorate of linguistics of the DPRK was awarded to Li Minde, dean of the Korean Language Faculty of Yanbian University of China.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He has taught and studied the Korean language, contributing to properly teaching it as required by the Pyongyang cultured language.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An awarding ceremony took place at the Mansudae Assembly Hall Friday.

Revolutionary Drama "Woman Comrade in Mt. Paektu" 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;�@Pyongyang, December 28 (KCNA) -- The revolutionary drama "Woman Comrade in Mt. Paektu" was performed before full houses at the State Dramatic Theater on the occasion of the 90th birth anniversary of anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk. The drama was reproduced by the State Theatrical Company.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@The story develops against the background of the large unit circling operation in the area northeast of Mt. Paektu which was organized and commanded by President Kim Il Sung from the autumn of Juche 28 (1939) to the next spring.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Kim Jong Suk, who always did everything she could for the safety of the President, goes down to an enemy-controlled area at the risk of her life to get to the bottom of the enemy's wicked scheme to do harm to the headquarters of the revolution and hurls herself into brave and subtle activities with her superb wisdom and unexampled courage.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Through her portrayal, the drama presents on an impressive artistic canvas the truth that it is the noble duty and conscience of a revolutionary soldier to defend the leader devotedly, which one should do of one's own accord till death, not on other's order.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@It also tells the historical lesson that anyone who pursues an easygoing and gay life, unsteady in revolutionary faith and will, turns into a betrayer and an apostate of the revolution without exception and that the gun muzzle of the enemy is always pointed at the headquarters of the revolution first.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@The drama deeply engraves in the mind of the Korean people the noble revolutionary life and the feats of Kim Jong Suk who provided the brilliant tradition of defending the leader devotedly.

Kim Jong Suk's Revolutionary Life to Be Always Remembered 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 28 (KCNA) -- The immortal revolutionary career of anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk and her fighting exploits will always be remembered by the Korean people and shine long, says Rodong Sinmun Friday in a signed article.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Suk's life was the most brilliant life of a great revolutionary, great patriot and great human being, the article notes, and goes on:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The glorious history of President Kim Il Sung in which he led the army and people of the DPRK to the path of victory in the van of the revolution is closely associated with the heroic feats performed by Kim Jong Suk as she took the lead in devotedly defending him in the grimmest period of the Korean revolution.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Suk's life was one of a great servicewoman and a noble life as she rendered distinguished service for bolstering the defence capacity of the country as an iron wall. It was none other than Kim Jong Suk who keenly realized how precious arms were and took the lead in resolutely defending the President's idea of attaching importance to the arms.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Suk was a great legendary woman as she provided an eternal boon to the victorious advance of the country and the revolution and its prosperity.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The tradition of the single-minded unity based on the revolutionary comradeship is the most valuable revolutionary legacy bequeathed to the people of the DPRK by Kim Jong Suk.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The revolutionary comradeship displayed by her meant the purest and most intense loyalty to the leader and total dedication to the comrades as her love for them was profound enough to bring a plant into bloom even on a stone and unhesitatingly risk her life for them.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Another precious revolutionary legacy she bequeathed to the people of the DPRK was the unshakable fighting spirit of weathering out whatever difficulties and ordeals.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The greatest historical feat she performed for the country and the people was that she provided a firm guarantee for successfully accomplishing the revolutionary cause of Juche generation after generation.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The army and people of the DPRK led by Kim Jong Il are victoriously advancing the revolutionary cause of Juche started on Mt. Paektu. It is thanks to Kim Jong Suk that the army and people of the DPRK are blessed with the illustrious leaders generation after generation, concludes the article.

Successes in Land Management Work 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;�@Pyongyang, December 28 (KCNA) -- Many successes have been registered in the land management work in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea this year.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Each unit has fulfilled its plan of land management including the production and transplantation of saplings, river improvement project, repair of the dykes for controlling tidewater, afforestation for land erosion control and road construction.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Hundreds of millions of trees including acacia, pine-nut trees, Pinus rigida and larch trees were planted everywhere in the country.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@People in Pyongyang City and North Hwanghae, South Phyongan and Kangwon provinces planted fast-growing trees of good species in mountains and fields, major roads, villages and parks.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Those in Chosan County of Jagang Province newly created 15 hectares of nursery fields for mixed forest and produced lots of saplings of good species.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Yonthan and Unpha Counties of North Hwanghae Province, Pyoksong County of South Hwanghae Province and other regions fixed right soils and made a large acreage of mixed forests by properly combining the pine-nut trees, larch trees, acacias and other kinds of trees with each other.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@This year unprecedented big floods hit the country two times, damaging rivers and streams. However, people in Hyangsan County of North Phyongan Province, Kumgang County of Kangwon Province, Phyongsan County of North Hwanghae Province and all other areas carried out projects of filling dyke, laying stones and dredging river-beds, restoring the rivers and streams to their original state.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Jagang, South Hamgyong, South Phyongan and other provinces, Kim Chaek City, Kosan County, Thaechon County and other cities and counties exerted efforts to the technical improvement of roads and thus ensured the safety of motorcar service and raised the traffic capacity.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Besides, similar projects were undertaken in various other counties to improve overall road conditions of the country.

Multi-Media E-Dictionary Produced
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 28 (KCNA) -- A multi-media E-dictionary "large literary and art dictionary" was compiled and produced by the Academy of Social Sciences.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The dictionary contains at least 14,500 entries, more than 6,800 image files and over 780 sound files which help deeply understand the successes made by the Juche-oriented literature and arts and world literature and arts.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It has many famous works published by President Kim Il Sung and leader Kim Jong Il while leading the field of literature and arts and masterpieces such as poems and songs, revolutionary operas and dramas created by the three generals of Mt. Paektu and explanations about them.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The dictionary also contains works and other writings done by members of the revolutionary family of the President in Mangyongdae.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It deals in detail with information about famous creators of Korea and various other countries of the world from the ancient times to the modern ones and literary and art works written by them.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This huge dictionary helps its users quickly and correctly search required files by diverse methods.

Kim Jong Il's Work Posted on Internet
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 28 (KCNA) -- The Central Committee of the All-Union Communist Party of Bolsheviks posted on its Internet homepage the full text of leader Kim Jong Il's work "The Workers' Party of Korea Is the Party of the Great Leader Comrade Kim Il Sung."&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This work, published on October 2, Juche 84 (1995), serves as the immortal guidelines of party building and activities as it reviewed with high pride the glorious history of the WPK, which pioneered a new road of building a revolutionary party in the era of independence under the leadership of President Kim Il Sung, and indicated the ways for developing the WPK into the eternal party of Kim Il Sung.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The homepage carried a photo of Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il.

DPRK's Important Days Celebrated
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 28 (KCNA) -- Symposiums, film shows and photo exhibitions were held by the Left United Party of Romania and the Khmer Democratic Party of Cambodia on December 20 and 21 on the occasions of the 16th anniversary of leader Kim Jong Il's assumption of the supreme commandership of the Korean People's Army and the 90th birth anniversary of anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On display at the venues of the functions were works of President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il and photos showing the exploits performed by Kim Jong Il in leading the Songun revolution.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Niculae Pavelescu, chairman of the Executive Committee of the Left United Party of Romania, said at the symposium that Kim Jong Il has developed the KPA into an army strong in ideology and faith and the invincible revolutionary armed forces and strengthened its military technical might in every way.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The greatest exploit performed by Kim Jong Suk is that she resolutely defended Kim Il Sung and brought up Kim Jong Il to be a distinguished leader who would steer the future of Korea.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The vice-chairman of the party said that the exploits performed by Kim Jong Suk, woman commander of Mt. Paektu, will be cherished in the hearts of the world people forever.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ouk Phurik, president of the Khmer Democratic Party of Cambodia, highly praised Kim Jong Il as a great strategist possessed of rare wisdom and outstanding leadership ability.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Korean documentary "They Were Together on the Road of the Great Songun Leadership" was appreciated at the film shows.

Removal of Concrete Wall Demanded in India
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, December 28 (KCNA) -- J.K.Patel, director of the Indian Institute for Foreign Policy Studies, released a statement on December 21 demanding the removal of the concrete wall.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement said that the concrete wall is an anti-reunification physical wall artificially blocking the reunification of Korea and the peace on the Korean Peninsula as it runs counter to the "Declaration on the Development of the North-South Relations and Peace and Prosperity".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is zealously patronizing the anti-reunification forces in south Korea and putting a brake on the development of the north-south relations and peace and prosperity on the Korean Peninsula, afraid of the possible breach in this barrier of division, the statement noted, demanding the U.S. drop its hostile policy towards the DPRK, away from the outdated way of thinking, stop instigating the anti-reunification forces of south Korea any longer and quit there as  early as possible taking all its forces and war equipment with it.

Rodong Sinmun censura la compleja situacion politica de Japon
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;�@Pyongyang, 28 de diciembre (ATCC) -- Si en Japon hubieran los politicos que conozcan la politica y tengan la vision de largo alcance, ellos deberian establecer la correcta concepcion de la historia, analizar correctamente los problemas y seguir la corriente de la epoca.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Asi senala el periodico Rodong Sinmun en un articulo individual del dia 28 y continua:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Como insiste la justa opinion publica del mundo, la primera tarea de Japon es liquidar lo mas pronto posible su ignominioso pasado, lo cual deviene la responsabilidad juridica y moral de este pais isleno asumida ante la epoca y la historia.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Los crimenes de los imperialistas japoneses perpetrados en el pasado en la agresion a Corea no pueden ser encubiertos de ninguna manera sino deben ser liquidados sin falta aunque pase mucho tiempo.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Pero, los reaccionarios japoneses se niegan obstinadamente a arrepentirse y disculparse por esas fechorias y al contrario, se valen de todas las artimanas para dejarlas en el olvido de la historia.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Un ejemplo de ello es que la capa gobernante y las fracciones partidistas de Japon pasan mucho tiempo discutiendo el problema de la aprobacion del nuevo "proyecto de ley de medidas especiales antiterroristas", pero nunca hacen referencia alguna a la expiacion de esos crimenes del pasado.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Si hubiera entre ellos algun politico con vision al futuro, deberia debatir las politicas abogando por la nueva partida de Japon basada en la liquidacion completa de los crimenes de guerra del siglo pasado.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Japon debe ver correctamente el mundo con el sentido contemporaneo y comenzar de nuevo ante la historia, en lugar de andar dejando estelas de sus asquerosas politicas militaristas.

Kim Jong Il recibe cesto de flores de familia de Zhang Weihua
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;�@Pyongyang, 28 de diciembre (ATCC) -- El Dirigente Kim Jong Il recibio un cesto de flores que le dedicara el dia 28 la familia de Zhang Weihua, martir revolucionario antijapones en ocasion del Ano Nuevo el 97 (2008) de la Era Juche.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@En la cinta del cesto se lee: "Deseamos de todo corazon buena salud al gran Dirigente, camarada  Kim Jong Il".

Kim Jong Il recibe felicitacion de  agregados militares en Corea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;�@Pyongyang, 28 de diciembre (ATCC) -- El Dirigente Kim Jong Il recibio un cesto de flores y una carta de felicitacion que el Cuerpo de Agregados Militares acreditado en Corea le dirigiera con motivo del Ano Nuevo el 97 (2008) de la Era Juche.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@El agregado militar de la Embajada de la Republica Socialista de Vietnam quien preside al cuerpo, Dau Xuan Long, los entrego el dia 28 a un funcionario coreano.

Exitos logrados en la administracion territorial
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;�@Pyongyang, 28 de diciembre (ATCC) -- Este ano, Corea logro muchos exitos en la administracion territorial.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Quedaron cumplidos a escala nacional los proyectos por ramas de esa labor, incluyendo la cria y plantacion de las posturas de arbol, el arreglo de fuentes fluviales, la reparacion de malecon, la obra del control hidraulico para prevenir la erosion y la construccion de carreteras.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En todas partes del pais fueron plantados cientos de millones de arboles como la acacia, el pino pinonero, el Pino canariensis y el alerce.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En particular, los habitantes de la ciudad de Pyongyang, las provincias de Hwanghae del Norte, de Phyong-an del Sur y de Kangwon sembraron los arboles de rapido crecimiento en los montes, llanuras, principales vias, aldeas y parques.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En el distrito de Chosan de la provincia de Jagang se produjeron muchas posturas de arboles de buena variedad en un nuevo vivero de 15 hectareas nuevamente acondicionado para crear los bosques mixtos.
  En los distritos de Yonthan y Unpha de la provincia de Hwanghae del Norte, el distrito de Pyoksong de la provincia de Hwanghae del  Sur y otras regiones se crearon extensos bosques mixtos al ubicar en terrenos adecuados el pino pinonero, el alerce y la acacia, entre otras plantas.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Aunque ocasionaron grandes perdidas en los recursos fluviales las inundaciones sin precedentes que azotaron este ano al pais en dos ocasiones, el distrito de Hyangsan de la provincia de Phyong-an del Norte, el distrito de Kumgang de la provincia de Kangwon, el distrito de Phyongsan de la provincia de Hwanghae del Norte y otras localidades los recuperaron en statu quo mediante la construccion del terraplen, el revestimiento con piedras y el dragado.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Al prestar mucha atencion a la renovacion tecnica de las carreteras, las provincias de Jagang, de Hamgyong del Sur y de Phyong-an del  Sur, la ciudad de Kim Chaek, los distritos de Kosan y Thaechon y otras provincias, ciudades y distritos garantizaron la seguridad del transito de automoviles y elevaron el porcentaje de su circulacion.
